===== Memory Tuning Decision =====

Detected Workload Type : swap-heavy
Baseline bogo ops/s    : 169102.70
Reason                 : High swap activity: si+so = 31930.3 KB/s

Parameter                           Bad Baseline    Tuned          
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  vm.swappiness                     200             10             
  vm.vfs_cache_pressure             500             100            
  vm.dirty_ratio                    5               20             
  vm.dirty_background_ratio         2               10             
  vm.min_free_kbytes                16384           262144         
  THP                               never           always         

--- Applying Tuning Commands Automatically ---

  [APPLY] sudo sysctl -w vm.swappiness=10
          ✓ Done

  [APPLY] sudo sysctl -w vm.vfs_cache_pressure=100
          ✓ Done

  [APPLY] sudo sysctl -w vm.dirty_ratio=20
          ✓ Done

  [APPLY] sudo sysctl -w vm.dirty_background_ratio=10
          ✓ Done

  [APPLY] sudo sysctl -w vm.min_free_kbytes=262144
          ✓ Done

  [APPLY] echo always | sudo tee /sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage/enabled
          ✓ Done

--- All Tuning Applied ---

--- Reasons ---
  - High swap activity: si+so = 31930.3 KB/s
  - swappiness=10: minimize anonymous page eviction (was 200 — 20× reduction)
  - vfs_cache_pressure=100: balanced eviction policy
  - dirty_ratio=20/10: allow write buffering to reduce flush-triggered eviction (was 5/2)
  - min_free_kbytes=262144: early reclaim trigger prevents sudden stalls (was 16384 — 16× increase)
  - THP=always: 2MB pages reduce TLB pressure for bulk anon allocations (was never)
